Like most things I post here, I wanted this model, so I made it, and I hope someone finds it useful too! It's about 50% taller than a normal ork, around 36mm at the head. He needs at least a 32mm base, but 40mm looks better.

This model couldn't have happened without the amazing models from this source:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4532582

EDIT: I guess calling this model its proper GW name got it copywrite striked, so I took it down and am reloading it under its proper name.

ALSO, I fixed those hollow skulls!

UPDATE: added a fantasy version too because why not

I wanted some space goblins for playing [Grim Horizons](https://www.wargamevault.com/product/336867/Grim-Horizons--Adventures-Told-Through-Combat) so i made this remix from some available models. The figures are approximately 20mm tall without any base so should get scaled if they are not being used as small characters.

If you enjoy these models please consider [tipping me a coffee](https://www.paypal.me/dotplot1) to encourage creation of new designs and improving existing ones.

Note: all the backpacks, googles, grenades, and other bits are separate shells which can be easily removed using meshmixer or other modeling software if you don't want them.

Update: the download all button is now working so the temporary ZIP files have been removed.

With Orktober looming i wanted to print some of the Jazzmantis retro space orcs but needed additional weapon options so i put together this remix for them as shown in the photo's above. However, this post only contains the remixed weapon arms and users will need to download the wide assortment of bodies/heads that Jazzmantis offerers from the links below.

Modular kit includes rifles, carbines, shotguns, pistols, melee weapons, grenades, and various special weapons.

Note: users will need to mirror some arms and Zip files are used for organisation.

If you enjoy these models please consider [tipping me a coffee](https://www.paypal.me/dotplot1) to encourage creation of new designs and improving existing ones.

As not all the remixed weapon came from thingiverse you can find them here:
Jazzmantis Bodies/Heads: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4532582
Ork Boltgun: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/old-ork-boltgun
Ork Sword: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/old-ork-powersword

Took Vidovic's fantastic gobbos and used them to make guardsmen for my grotguard army.

You'll notice that many of the grots look like they are wearing platform shoes, this is because my crappy printer misses the first mm when printing, so I had to do that to compensate. You'll need to file those down, or hide it with basing material, or just fix it in blender.

This is a remix from https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:398515

I love Big Mek from PC-game "Dawn of war", so made the model based on this character. 28mm scale.

There are a lot of separeted parts - for better casting. And you can print the most detailed parts on a high-quality expensive printer, and other on a cheaper machine.

About the photos: 2nd and 3d - just for scale. The grey parts was printed at Formlabs 2 (or "1" - i dont know), the orange - i dont know. Casted by some guys. 360 video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgVGTmzWm9c.

(And i fixed some things in the model liiitle bit after printing and rendering - so there is better version, pictures are old)

NON COMMERCIAL of course
